# npm 11.11.0 — transitive dependency CVEs (fixed upstream, awaiting npm release)
#
# Fixes exist in minimatch >=10.2.3 and tar >=7.5.10, but these are
# bundled inside npm itself. We cannot bump them independently; they
# will be resolved when a new npm release updates its transitive deps.
# All three are DoS-class issues that require crafted input, carrying
# no practical risk in a CI context with trusted inputs.

# minimatch: ReDoS via unbounded recursive backtracking (fixed in 10.2.3)
CVE-2026-27903

# minimatch: ReDoS via catastrophic backtracking in glob expressions (fixed in 10.2.3)
CVE-2026-27904

# node-tar: vulnerability in tar <7.5.10
CVE-2026-29786
